Sister city

Sequim has a [sister city](/Sister_city) relationship with [Shiso, Hyōgo](/Shiso,_Hy%C5%8Dgo), Japan. The city originally signed a sister city agreement in June 1993 with [Yamasaki, Hyōgo](/Yamasaki,_Hy%C5%8Dgo), which merged with several municipalities to form Shiso in 2005. &#91;100&#93; &#91;101&#93; The two cities operate a short-term [exchange student](/Exchange_student) program through Sequim's high school and middle school. &#91;102&#93; &#91;103&#93;

